# Claude (opus) — 2026-03-17 11:20:28
# Duration: 326s — Exit: 0
# Prompt:
#   /spec:create Improve title extraction algorithm based on feedback from iteration 27
#   
#   Context for spec creation:
#   - Read the feedback at tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/feedback.md
#   - Read the current implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts
#   - Read previous iteration docs in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand what has been tried
#   
#   Hard constraints:
#   - Must run on a mobile device (React Native / Expo)
#   - Total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds
#   - Changes land in lib/text-classifier/ and related files
#   
#   Everything else is open for debate. The current approach (MiniLM embeddings + heuristic scoring)
#   is one option, but you are free to propose alternatives if they'd work better:
#   - Different embedding model or similarity strategy
#   - Replacing embeddings entirely with a rule-based or hybrid approach
#   - Restructuring the pipeline (e.g., two-pass, re-ranking, candidate merging)
#   - Changing how candidates are generated, filtered, or deduplicated
#   - Any other approach that solves the failures within the hard constraints
#   
#   Don't be incremental for the sake of it — if the feedback reveals a fundamental design flaw,
#   propose a fundamental fix. But also don't change things that already work well.
#   
#   IMPORTANT: Write the spec to tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/improvement-plan.md (not to specs/ directory).
#   Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the improvement-plan.md file.

============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/improvement-plan.md`.

The plan proposes 4 targeted fixes matching the 4 failure patterns, ordered by impact:

1. **OCR blind repair** (5 cases) — Apply blind digit→letter substitution *before* embedding for early-position candidates, so `Bra1sed` → `Braised` gets a good embedding score
2. **Multi-line dedup protection** (1 case) — When the longer candidate is a 2-line join and its suffix is a food word, keep the longer form instead of preferring the shorter prefix
3. **Post-header title promotion** (3 cases) — Add a "direct-successor" bonus when a candidate immediately follows a filtered section header or metadata line
4. **Spillover detection** (2 cases) — Lower the instruction-prologue skip threshold from 5→3, and restrict corroboration to post-spillover lines so foreign recipe titles don't get vocabulary support from spillover content

No architectural changes proposed — the current approach works for 90%+ of cases. Each fix is scoped to minimize regression risk.
