{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H3GLYvz2xWC6LXKtS4mrWe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the data I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction Iteration History (Iterations 24-27)\n\n### Overall Trajectory\n\nThe title extractor has made **steady, measurable progress** over the past 4 iterations, particularly on real-world files:\n\n| Iteration | Overall Score | Real Files | Generated Files | Key Status |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------|-----------------|-----------|\n| 24        | 83.8%         | 18 failures | 0 passing       | Baseline with heavy OCR corruption issues |\n| 25        | 100% (real)   | 1 failure  | 0 passing       | **Breakthrough**: Real file performance perfected |\n| 26        | 85.6%         | 0 failures | 16 failures     | Real files solid; focus on synthetic test coverage |\n| 27        | 90.1%         | 0 failures | 11 failures     | Real files maintained; synthetic test improvements |\n\n**Key insight from iter.txt**: Iteration 25 achieved perfect performance on the 11 real test files (100.0%), which has been maintained through iterations 26-27.\n\n---\n\n### Recurring Failure Patterns\n\nFive core issues persist across iterations 24-27, though their impact has shifted:\n\n#### 1. **OCR digit-for-letter corruption (5 cases — RECURRING)**\n   - Examples: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne`, `P1ern1k z Śliwkami`, `Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p`\n   - Behavior: Line-1 title rejected entirely; extractor returns empty or picks garbage text\n   - Iterations: Present in 24, 26, 27 (not uniquely addressed)\n   - **Root cause**: The extractor applies digit-corruption penalties that disqualify otherwise-title-shaped lines, especially when multiple substitutions (1→i, 4→a) are clustered\n   - **Why hard to fix**: A line like `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne` is structurally sound (right length, capitalization, position) but fails hard filters or embedding quality checks due to corruption density\n\n#### 2. **Category/section headers preceding titles (3 cases — RECURRING)**\n   - Examples: `FISH & SEAFOOD` / title, `VEGETABLES` / title, metadata line `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...` / title\n   - Behavior: Section header picked instead of title, or title skipped entirely; returns body instruction or empty\n   - Iterations: Present in 24, 26, 27\n   - **Root cause**: All-caps short headers (1-3 words) score too high in embedding similarity; pipe-delimited metadata not reliably recognized as non-title\n   - **Why persistent**: Heuristic tries to skip these but doesn't reliably promote the immediately-following line as the real title\n\n#### 3. **Spillover / mid-recipe page starts (2-5 cases — RECURRING)**\n   - Examples: Page starts with `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER...]` or mid-ingredient list with no title present\n   - Behavior: Returns empty, random body line, or a different recipe's title buried in the file\n   - Iterations: 5 cases in iter 26 (Pattern A); 2 cases in iter 27 (Pattern 4)\n   - **Why hard**: Title may genuinely not exist on the current page; multi-recipe pages create ambiguity\n\n#### 4. **Multi-line title splits (1 case — RECURRING)**\n   - Example: `LEMON HERB RO45TED` / `VEGETABLES` → extracts only first line\n   - Behavior: Title candidate is short, next line is all-caps continuation; treated independently\n   - Iterations: Present in 24, 26, 27\n   - **Why persistent**: No downstream logic to detect and merge short title + short continuation pattern\n\n#### 5. **Incorrect body text extraction over corrupted title (3 cases — RECURRING)**\n   - Examples: Picking serving instructions or garbage tokens over the actual (corrupted) title\n   - Behavior: Title rejected due to corruption, then first \"sentence-like\" body line selected\n   - Iterations: Present in 24, 26, 27\n   - **Why persistent**: Once title line is rejected, no positional enforcement to prefer earlier lines\n\n---\n\n### Fixed / Improved Patterns\n\n#### Successfully Resolved:\n1. **Compound title with `:` or `+` separators** (2 failures in iter 24 → 0 in iter 26-27)\n   - Examples: `HERB ROASTED PORK : VARIATION`, `PIERNIK TRADYCYJNY + NOWOCZESNY`\n   - Fix: Likely adjusted scoring or candidate generation to keep full compound titles\n\n2. **Polish title + English subtitle** (1 failure in iter 24 → 0 in iter 26-27)\n   - Example: `Golonka` / `Roasted Pork Knuckle` → now extracts `Golonka` correctly\n   - Fix: Possibly improved short-title handling or positional bonuses\n\n3. **Bilingual title confusion** (Iter 25 had 1 real-file failure with OCR artifact)\n   - Fix: Applied mitigation to prefer vocabulary-correlated candidates over orphaned all-caps strings\n   - Status: One-time real failure; pattern appears solved\n\n---\n\n### Iteration-Specific Insights\n\n**Iteration 24 (baseline, 83.8%)**\n- 18 generated-file failures, 0 real-file failures\n- 7 distinct failure patterns identified\n- Issues span OCR corruption, section headers, and multi-recipe pages\n\n**Iteration 25 (BREAKTHROUGH)**\n- **Only 1 real-file failure** out of 11 tested (100% overall, 90.9% generated)\n- Single failure pattern: OCR artifact (`DAT FLATBREADS`) mistaken for title component in compound title\n- Clear evidence: Major fixes applied between iter 24 and 25; unknown what changed\n\n**Iteration 26 (85.6%)**\n- 0 real-file failures maintained\n- 16 generated-file failures, largely synthetic test cases\n- Failure patterns refined into 6 categories (A–F)\n- Many failures are edge cases (\"corrupted spillover,\" \"mid-recipe starts\") that may not reflect real-world scans\n\n**Iteration 27 (90.1%)**\n- 0 real-file failures maintained\n- 11 generated-file failures (4 fewer than iter 26)\n- Same 4 core patterns still failing, but reduced frequency\n- Improvements: Fixed Mushroom Risotto (iter 26: wrong recipe title → iter 27: correct partial), Sweet Potato Salad, Spinach Pie, Zupa Koperkowa, Bigos Myśliwski\n\n---\n\n### Highest-Impact Recurring Issues (Priority for Further Work)\n\n| Pattern | Iter 24 | Iter 26 | Iter 27 | Real-world Relevance | Suggested Fix Direction |\n|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------------------|----------------------|\n| OCR digit corruption | 4 cases | 2 cases | 5 cases | **HIGH** — real scans have this | Lower digit-corruption penalty for line-1 candidates; semantic validation |\n| Section headers | 3 cases | 3 cases | 3 cases | **HIGH** — cookbook layouts common | Recognize & skip headers; promote following line; metadata pattern detection |\n| Spillover/mid-recipe | — | 5 cases | 2 cases | **MEDIUM** — page crops miss titles | Detect spillover markers; scan forward for first standalone title |\n| Multi-line title splits | 1 case | 1 case | 1 case | **MEDIUM** — layouts sometimes split | Merge short line + short all-caps continuation |\n| Body text over corrupted title | 3 cases | 3 cases | 3 cases | **MEDIUM** — bad OCR pages exist | Enforce positional preference (line 1 > body) even with corruption |\n\n---\n\n### Overall Assessment\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Real file performance has been stabilized at 100% across iterations 25-27\n- Major compound-title issue fixed\n- Architecture is sound (multi-stage heuristics + embeddings)\n\n**Persistent challenges:**\n- Generated-file test suite reveals recurring edge cases that are hard to solve without changing core heuristics\n- OCR digit corruption, section headers, and spillover cases form an irreducible minimum of difficult cases\n- Some failures are on synthetic test data that may not reflect real cookbook OCR\n\n**Trajectory:**\n- **Upward trend on real files**: 0% → 90.9% (iter 24) → 100% (iter 25) → sustained 100%\n- **Plateau on generated files**: Improvements are incremental; core patterns repeat\n- **Risk of regression**: Over-tuning on synthetic tests (iter 26-27) hasn't harmed real-file performance so far"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a02df25fd8fd2c2d5 (for resuming t