{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0139U6A1D6UT8jzw6jqAV3aX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/improvement-plan.md`.\n\nThe plan proposes 4 targeted fixes matching the 4 failure patterns, ordered by impact:\n\n1. **OCR blind repair** (5 cases) — Apply blind digit→letter substitution *before* embedding for early-position candidates, so `Bra1sed` → `Braised` gets a good embedding score\n2. **Multi-line dedup protection** (1 case) — When the longer candidate is a 2-line join and its suffix is a food word, keep the longer form instead of preferring the shorter prefix\n3. **Post-header title promotion** (3 cases) — Add a \"direct-successor\" bonus when a candidate immediately follows a filtered section header or metadata line\n4. **Spillover detection** (2 cases) — Lower the instruction-prologue skip threshold from 5→3, and restrict corroboration to post-spillover lines so foreign recipe titles don't get vocabulary support from spillover content\n\nNo architectural changes proposed — the current approach works for 90%+ of cases. Each fix is scoped to minimize regression risk."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6095,"cache_read_input_tokens":62717,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6095},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"67c804db-4061-40f8-823f-56265230248d","uuid":"eacdd526-d0a8-4b14-9f38-c4cd01e1f6b1"}
